WEBVTT

00:08:27.919 --> 00:08:31.117
AG: Oh, and the 700 dollars
Pejman spent on calls to Iran

00:08:31.141 --> 00:08:34.302
paid off, too -- he ended up
marrying his girlfriend.

00:08:34.326 --> 00:08:36.843
They just celebrated
their 25th anniversary.

00:08:38.470 --> 00:08:40.677
So who you know tomorrow
will depend in part

00:08:40.701 --> 00:08:42.327
on what you know today.

00:08:42.862 --> 00:08:45.113
Becoming an expert
can help you meet people

00:08:45.137 --> 00:08:48.093
and give them a reason
to want you in their networks.

00:08:48.117 --> 00:08:51.609
But that's not the only way
to move beyond swapping business cards.

00:08:51.633 --> 00:08:54.586
Reid Hoffman: I hate what people
normally think of networking.

00:08:54.610 --> 00:08:55.808
AG: That's Reid Hoffman.

00:08:55.832 --> 00:08:57.466
RH: I'm the cofounder of LinkedIn,

00:08:57.490 --> 00:09:00.561
and I'm a host of
the "Masters of Scale" podcast.